# Protei_Bulk Temporary Directory

This directory contains temporary and runtime working data for Protei_Bulk.

## Subdirectories:
- cache/: Cached data for performance optimization
- parser/: Temporary files during message parsing
- buffer/: Message buffers and queues

## Runtime Files:
- protei_bulk.pid: Process ID file (created at runtime)
- *.lock: Lock files for synchronization
- *.sock: Unix socket files for IPC

## Cleanup:
- Temporary files are automatically cleaned up on shutdown
- Manual cleanup: Run scripts/utils/cleanup_tmp.sh
- Cache files older than 7 days are automatically removed
- Parser and buffer files older than 1 day are removed

## Important:
- Do not manually delete files while application is running
- Ensure sufficient disk space for temporary operations
- This directory should be on a fast disk (SSD preferred)
- Files in this directory are NOT backed up

## Permissions:
- Directory should be writable by application user
- PID file requires read/write access
- Recommended permissions: 755 (rwxr-xr-x)
